==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Elusive
<hw>E*lu"sive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Tending to elude;
using arts or deception to escape; adroitly escaping or evading; eluding
the grasp; fallacious.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Elusive</qex> of the bridal day, she gives⟦br⟧
Fond hopes to all, and all with hopes deceives.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>E*lu"sive*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>E*lu"sive*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Elusory</ent>⟦br⟧
